"Bravo!
Bravo!"
cried
Tristouse
clapping
her
hands,
"A
statue

out
of
nothing,
empty,
that's
lovely,
and
when
will
you
make
it?"

"Tomorrow,
if
you
wish;
we
shall
go
and
dine,
pass
the
night

together,
and
in
the
morning
we
shall
go
to
the
Meudon
woods
where

I
shall
make
this
profound
statue."

No
sooner

than
done.
